messages.title: Election Messaging
messages.content: Five more years of Theresa May means a more heartless and divided Britain. Corbyn's Labour is too weak and divided to win this election. On 8th June change Britainâ€™s future. Vote Liberal Democrat.

issues.brexitEurope: Labour voted with UKIP and Tories for Brexit. LABOUR'S BREXIT BETRAYAL.

images.caption: Political figures with statements indicating positions on Brexit

leaflet.additionalNotes: The leaflet focuses on Brexit and portrays Labour as having betrayed their stance by voting with UKIP and Tories. There are no specific policies or personal statements of the Liberal Democrat candidate, nor contact information or endorsements provided in the provided image of the leaflet. The candidate and party leader of the Liberal Democrats are not named in the leaflet.
